Terrible & deserves ZERO stars. Using the Sloce app, I ordered a large pepperoni with extra cheese, penne a la vodka, a calzone & pinwheels. This was my 2nd time trying this place after a mediocre initial taste & figured extra cheese might solve my problems. I‚Äôve never owned a pizzeria, however, objectively, this place uses so little cheese on their pizza, that their extra cheese option, which costs $2, still doesn‚Äôt come close to a regular serving of cheese at other local pizzerias. After speaking with the people at slice, they confirmed that their vodka sauce is tomato sauce & heavy cream, which I personally find to be an affront to Italian cuisine everywhere. Naturally, the pasta also had very little ‚Äúvodka‚Äù sauce & the added chicken was bland at best. If I had a nonna, she‚Äôd be appalled. The pinwheels also had a meager serving of cheese with maybe 3 pepperonis at the center? Lastly, the calzone had sausage that was bright red & the taste was reminiscent of school lunch circa 1998. The food this place serves is atrocious. Bring your business elsewhere.
